               <msContents>
                  <summary>I)	Zenā ḥǝmāmātihu la-madḫanina “Story of the Passion of Our Saviour” (fols. 4ra-32r) (cf. Ms. BritLib Orient. 8819, StrBritLib 92-94, no. 57)&#xD;
I-1) Introductory prayer (rhyming) (fol. 4ra-vb) &#xD;
I-2) Homily for Monday (za-sänuy) (fols. 4vb-10vb) &#xD;
I-3) Homily for Tuesday (za-śälus) (fols. 10vb-15ra)&#xD;
I-4) Homily for Wednesday (za-räbuʿ) (fols. 15ra-20ra) &#xD;
I-5) Homily for Thursday (za-ḥamus) (fols. 20ra-24vb)&#xD;
I-6) Homily for Friday (za-ʾarb) (fols. 24vb-27vb) &#xD;
I-7) Homily for Saturday (za-qädam) (fols. 28ra-29va)&#xD;
I-8) Homily for Sunday (za-ʾǝḥud) (fols. 29va-30vb)&#xD;
I-9) Entrusting prayer (fols. 30va-32rb)&#xD;
II)	Maṣḥaf la-tazkāra madḫane ʿālam “Book for the Commemoration of the Saviour of the World” (fols. 34ra-74va) &#xD;
II-1) Introduction (fols. 34ra-35va)&#xD;
II-2) Gadla Mäbʿa Ṣǝyon “Vita of Mäbʿa Ṣǝyon (Takla Māryām)” (fols. 35va-70rb)&#xD;
II-3) Taʾāmra Mäbʿa Ṣǝyon “Miracles of Mäbʿa Ṣǝyon” (fols. 70rb-74va)&#xD;
&#xD;
Additio 1; colophon.</summary>
