                     <decoNote type="rubrication" xml:id="d0">Nomina sacra; names of the donor and his family members; name of the king; a few lines (alternating with black lines) on the incipit page of Texts I and II; two or three initial lines of sections of Texts I and II; donation note (fol. 32rb); name of the protagonist of Text II; some phrases and words in Text I; some corrections (e.g., fols. 13ra l.1, 15rb l.7); names of the weekdays (entire or elements) in Text I;  elements of punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</decoNote>
